			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Neriad Shawl question<a name="24474"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 28 04 7:57 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Track neriad princesses, as they are what drop the shawl.  I know there is at least one in the long underwatch passage in the southernmost part of the zone (look at the in-game map, if you've downloaded it).  I have never seen the shawl drop, but several folks here have.  This &quot;camp&quot; (if you can call it that, being that there are equally spaced mob spawn points all throughout this tunnel) is not soloable by any method I am familiar with, since it is underwater and everything hits VERY hard.  
<br />

<br />
I have led groups there several times since the revamp, with the hope of getting the shawl to drop.  You should bring a full group with you.  A 60+ warrior/pally/sk tank is REQUIRED.  We've tried tanks lower than that, and they were torn up.  I would recommend an SK tank, for corpse summons.  It is rare that you don't have at least one death, and if it happens to be the cleric (as was my case at least once) forget it.  Corpse summon is almost a necessity in this zone.
<br />

<br />
Good luck.
<br />

<br />
Mirthe
<br />
61 Bard
<br />
Quellious</span></td>
