				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Neriad Shawl question<a name="24958"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 2 04 12:18 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>How i did and yes solo'ed after revamp.  Zone in from WW side.  Invis and go down well.  Only spot with a possible see invis mob (seahorse).  At bottom of well go to tunnel that leads to a dead end with 3 neriads above you. Target one.  Back up to the hall way. Lull then use bind sight to target and lull the other 2.  Once all lulled pull one with charm/slow/whatever.  Have full battle buffs and DS ready.  Fight until low on health and mezz/heal. Repeat.  When they are low they will want to death creep.  I used the lower mez to pull them back and any DD (bellows, SSP, anything with DD) then remez and re-DD.  Keep doing until dead.  Heal up, re-lull and kill next.  Repeat.
<br />

<br />
Only one mob will spawn the princess.  The mob directly above the tunnel.
<br />
Hope that helps, the hardest part was landing mez before they got to the 3 mobs at bottom of well.  So keep them mezzed and pulled as far back as possible prior to DD.
<br />
</span></td>
